@sstern6 

> are all doc PRs done on webpackjs.org, or are there other repos where documentation is updated?

It's a mix... all loader and plugin readmes in the webpack-contrib organization's repos (and a few external repos) are pulled during the build. Issues and PRs to correct those documents would have to happen outside of the main repository. The voting app and analyze app are also external. Everything else though should be edited in the content directory. On the loader and plugin pages, there is a _Jump to Repository_ and _Edit Document_ pages that will bring you to the right place. You can also ping us if you're still unsure.

> ... as per the docs, import(/* webpackChunkName: "my-chunk-name" */ 'module'); as far as ive seen and understand there cannot be a space between the comment and the module...

Do you get an error when excluding the space? I'm using `import()` on a few projects and haven't seen any issues although I typically write it out like this:

``` javascript
import(
  /* webpackChunkName: "my-chunk" */
  './path/to/some/file'
)
```

